{{Quote|It seems obvious that your story has completely divorced itself from any semblance of reality.|[[Tru'eb Cholakk]]|<ref name="Starter's Tale">"Starter's Tale"</ref>}}
"'''Starter's Tale'''" was a short story written by [[Peter M. Schweighofer]] and illustrated by [[John Paul Lona]]. It was published in the [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 4|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 4]] by [[West End Games]] in [[November]] [[1994]].

==Plot summary==
The story was told from the perspective of [[Starter]], who elaborately detailed taking on the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] [[Beylyssa]], [[Boddu Bocck]], [[4-LOM/Legends|4-LOM]], [[Zuckuss/Legends|Zuckuss]], [[IG-88B/Legends|IG-88]] and [[Dengar/Legends|Dengar]] and defeating them single-handedly. He was then rendered unconscious by [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]], who delivered him to [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]]. Escaping Vader's clutches, Starter stole an Imperial shuttle, the ''[[Tydirium/Legends|Tydirium]]'', which he delivered to the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]].

